  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Deborah Weston heard a lecture by George Bradburn in the Universalist Meeting House. She reports on the beautiful arrangement, good spirits, and successful sale at the anti-slavery fair. She writes: &quot;All the fashionable had been in and bought extensively.&quot; Deborah has suffered from a painful face-ache, but left the seclusion of her chamber when John A. Collins called. She deprecates the attitude of the Episcopal minister who would not read a notice [of the anti-slavery fair?] on Sunday.</subfield>
